org.batfish.question.traceroute

Class TracerouteQuestion

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.batfish.datamodel.questions.Question
      • org.batfish.datamodel.questions.IPacketTraceQuestion
        • org.batfish.question.traceroute.TracerouteQuestion
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IQuestion

    public final class TracerouteQuestion
extends IPacketTraceQuestion
    A question to perform a traceroute.

    This question performs a virtual traceroute in the network from ingress node. The destination IP is randomly picked if not explicitly specified. Other IP headers are also randomly picked if unspecified, with a bias toward generating packets similar to a real traceroute (see below).

    Unlike a real traceroute, this traceroute is directional. That is, for it to succeed, the reverse connectivity is not needed. This feature can help debug connectivity issues by decoupling the two directions.
